        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Abolish Human Trafficking Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill sets forth a variety of measures to address the prevention and punishment of human trafficking and to assist trafficking victims. Included among these are provisions concerning:</p> <ul> <li>restitution for victims;</li> <li>funding of investigations of offenses relating to sexual abuse of children;</li> <li>grants to states and localities and other entities for victim service assistance;</li> <li>training of health, victim service, and federal law enforcement personnel, including through the use of a victim screening protocol by the Department of Homeland Security;</li> <li>penalties imposed for slavery offenses, sex trafficking of children, and repeat convictions for transportation for illegal sexual activity and related crimes;</li> <li>travel for the purpose of engaging in any illicit sexual conduct;</li> <li>designation of additional Department of Justice resources for prosecution and service coordination;</li> <li>penalties for offenses involving organized human trafficking, sexual abuse, sexual exploitation, or transportation for prostitution or any illegal sexual activity; and</li> <li>studies of the physical and psychological effects of serious harm to victims.</li> </ul>]]></text>
      </summary>
